  For example:
  tri(2) = 1 + (2 / 2) = 2
  tri(4) = 3
  tri(3) = tri(2) + tri(1) + tri(4)
         = 2 + 3 + 3 = 8 
  You are given a non-negative integer number n, you have to a return a list of the 
  first n + 1 numbers of the Tribonacci sequence.
  Examples:
  tri(3) = [1, 3, 2, 8]
  */
const tri = (n) => {
  let a = 1, b = 1, c = 1;
  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    c = a + b;
    a = b;
    b = c;
  }
  return [...new Array(n + 1).fill(1),...new Array(n + 1).fill(c)];
};

